1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper presents an end-to-end object tracking approach using deep learning, which is a common topic in computer vision research. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper mentions that the proposed approach is designed to track objects in 2D laser data, which is commonly encountered in robotics applications. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a learning method based on a form of input dropout, which is a common technique in machine learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper presents an approach that uses deep learning to estimate the entire environment state in real-time, which is a common goal in artificial intelligence research. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses recurrent neural networks to learn a mapping from sensor measurements to object tracks, which falls under the category of neural computing.
